'''Carrots''' was a character in an unfinished and unpublished children's<ref name=chronology>{{CG|C}}, p. 125 (entry "17 March 1924")</ref> tale by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]].<ref name=Bio>{{B|IV}}, Chapter VI: The Storyteller, first paragraph</ref>

When the Tolkien family had moved in [[1924]]<ref name=chronology/> to 2 Darnley Road<ref name=chronology/> in Leeds, [[John Tolkien]] recalled that he often had difficulty falling asleep and his father would come to his bedside and tell stories to him. One of these tales was about a boy named Carrots, who had red hair and climbed "into a cuckoo clock" to go off on a series of strange adventures.<ref name=Bio/>

